- **~280 lines of `if phrase not in text`** — could be a 10-line loop over a `{file: [phrases]}` dict.
- **The entire 907-line script could be ~200 lines** with a data-driven approach: define checks as `(file, expected_phrases, expected_exists)` tuples, iterate once.
- The agent contract field checks (lines 620–700) and prompt phrase guards (lines 700–830) already use dict-based iteration — but the rest of the file doesn't follow the same pattern, making it inconsistent.
- **Hardcoded date-stamped benchmark doc paths** (lines 126–132) — `2026-03-12-first-place-strategy.md` etc. — these will silently break when the docs are renamed or dated differently.

