| `cc10x_harness_audit.py` | **Offline (indirectly live)** | Publication drift audit. Same indirect path. Checks file existence and string presence — not runtime behavior. |
| `cc10x_reference_benchmark.py` | **Dead code** | Zero references from any file. Duplicate of worldclass benchmark. |
| `cc10x_live_harness_runner.py` | **Plausibly live** | Verifier agent prompt instructs running it. But it's a generic subprocess wrapper — the bootstrap manifest it runs just calls the offline scripts. |

**Bottom line:** 0 of 5 scripts are in the direct live hook path. 1 is plausibly live (runner). 2 are indirectly live (via bootstrap manifest). 1 is offline-only. 1 is dead code.

